    "speaker": "interviewee",
    "tag": "HF",
    "text": "And this is a picture of my father, Hayim Mayer Frenkiel, spelled F-R-E-N-K-I-E-L, born on December 12, 1884, in Lodz, Poland. He was a manufacturer, textile manufacturer, specializing in weaving and finishing materials. Quite a successful businessman. Extremely good father and very thoughtful, a good companion to many of the people who benefited from his association. He, unfortunately, were separated during the war. And he died in Lodz Ghetto in-- on September 1, 1940.",
